This paper deals with sentiment analysis, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). The use of word embeddings and label propagation also suggests a focus on machine learning and data mining techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers NLP and machine learning for language processing. 

The paper also involves social media analysis, which falls under the sub-category cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The use of embeddings and label propagation also suggests a focus on unsupervised learning, which is covered by cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

The paper involves the use of historical data, which suggests a focus on information retrieval and data mining, covered by cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
